winpodx (0.1.5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Packaging: drop the Python >= 3.11 requirement to >= 3.9 so RHEL 9 and its
    rebuilds (AlmaLinux 9, Rocky 9) can install winpodx without the python3.11
    AppStream module. The only 3.11 blocker was stdlib tomllib; we now fall
    back to the pure-Python tomli package on 3.9/3.10 (marker-gated dep).
  * Packaging: depend on python3-tomli on Debian/Ubuntu so the fallback import
    works out-of-the-box regardless of the installed Python version.
  * CI: add Python 3.9 and 3.10 to the pytest matrix.
  * CI: new rhel-publish.yml workflow builds AlmaLinux 9 and 10 RPMs on tag
    push and attaches them to the GitHub release (mirrors the debs-publish
    matrix pattern).
  * CI: new aur-publish.yml workflow + packaging/aur/PKGBUILD template for
    Arch Linux AUR. Secret-gated on AUR_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY so tag pushes before
    the one-time AUR account/SSH setup skip cleanly. See
    packaging/aur/README.md for onboarding.
  * CI: obs-publish discover-and-download step now matches MirrorCache "./"
    href prefixes (the previous grep anchored on `href="winpodx-` and found
    zero RPMs after v0.1.4); also follows redirects with curl -L.

 -- Kim DaeHyun <kernalix7@kodenet.io>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 19:00:00 +0900

winpodx (0.1.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Packaging: drop debian/winpodx.install; pybuild pyproject plugin installs
    directly to debian/winpodx/ so the intermediate manifest was pointing at
    an empty debian/tmp and dh_install aborted with "missing files".
  * CI: obs-publish wait loop now inspects only <status package="winpodx"
    code="..."/> instead of any code="..." in the XML. Repo-level broken
    states (e.g. "nothing provides rpm" on Factory PowerPC ppc64 and Slowroll
    aarch64) are OBS infrastructure noise and no longer abort our publish.

 -- Kim DaeHyun <kernalix7@kodenet.io>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0900

winpodx (0.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Packaging: skip dh_auto_test during .deb build; tests run upstream in
    GitHub Actions CI across Python 3.11-3.13.
  * CI: obs-publish polls /public/build/... instead of /build/..., since the
    runservice token can only trigger services and OBS /build/ needs auth.

 -- Kim DaeHyun <kernalix7@kodenet.io>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 15:00:00 +0900

winpodx (0.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CI: obs-publish and debs-publish now trigger on tag push, not release:published,
    to bypass GitHub's recursive-workflow guard on GITHUB_TOKEN-created releases.
  * Packaging: RPM spec globs the dist-info directory in %files to tolerate
    pyproject.toml / git tag version drift between release bumps.

 -- Kim DaeHyun <kernalix7@kodenet.io>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0900

winpodx (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Packaging: drop debtransform from OBS _service; .deb built by GitHub Actions.
  * Packaging: RPM spec uses python313 on Leap 16.0 / Tumbleweed.
  * CI: check-windows-updates opens an Issue instead of a pull request.
  * Docs: install instructions cover openSUSE / Fedora / Debian / Ubuntu prebuilt packages.

